question: Calculate the highest common divisor of 117 and 676.
output:
We use the Euclidean algorithm to find the highest common divisor of 117 and 676. \begin{align*}
\gcd(117, 676) &= \gcd(676, 117 - 6 \cdot 117) \\
&= \gcd(676, 117) \\
&= \gcd(676 - 117 \cdot 5, 117) \\
&= \gcd(135, 117) \\
&= \gcd(135, 117 - 135 \cdot 1) \\
&= \gcd(135, 117 - 135) \\
&= \gcd(135, 117 - 135 \cdot 1) \\
&= \gcd(135, 117 - 135) \\
&= \gcd(135, 0) \\
\end{align*}The highest common divisor of 117 and 676 is $\boxed{1}$. The answer is 1
